\p
\v 1 \w A|strong="H3068"\w* \w prophecy|strong="H4853"\w*:\f + \fr 1:1 \ft Literally, “burden.”\f* \w This|strong="H1697"\w* \w message|strong="H1697"\w* \w came|strong="H3478"\w* \w from|strong="H3478"\w* \w the|strong="H3068"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w* \w concerning|strong="H4853"\w* \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* \w through|strong="H3027"\w* \w Malachi|strong="H4401"\w*.   
\p
\v 2 \w I|strong="H3808"\w* \w have|strong="H3068"\w* loved\f + \fr 1:2 \ft The tense of the verb indicates not just a past action but a past action that continues in the present.\f* \w you|strong="H3808"\w*, \w says|strong="H5002"\w* \w the|strong="H5002"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w*.  
\p \w But|strong="H3808"\w* \w you|strong="H3808"\w* ask, “\w How|strong="H4100"\w* \w have|strong="H3068"\w* \w you|strong="H3808"\w* loved us?”  
\p Wasn't \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w* \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w*'s brother? \w the|strong="H5002"\w* \w Lord|strong="H3068"\w* responds. \w But|strong="H3808"\w* \w I|strong="H3808"\w* loved \w Jacob|strong="H3290"\w*  
\v 3 \w and|strong="H2022"\w* \w despised|strong="H8130"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*. \w I|strong="H7760"\w* \w have|strong="H4057"\w* \w made|strong="H7760"\w* \w Esau|strong="H6215"\w*'s \w mountain|strong="H2022"\w* homeland \w into|strong="H7760"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w wasteland|strong="H4057"\w*, \w and|strong="H2022"\w* \w turned|strong="H7760"\w* \w his|strong="H7760"\w* \w inheritance|strong="H5159"\w* \w into|strong="H7760"\w* \w a|strong="H3068"\w* \w desert|strong="H4057"\w* \w for|strong="H8077"\w* jackals.   
\p
\v 4 \w The|strong="H3588"\w* \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \w of|strong="H3068"\w* Edom \w may|strong="H3068"\w* \w be|strong="H3068"\w* saying: “\w We|strong="H3588"\w* \w have|strong="H3068"\w* \w been|strong="H5769"\w* \w beaten|strong="H7567"\w* \w down|strong="H2040"\w*, \w but|strong="H3588"\w* \w we|strong="H3068"\w* \w will|strong="H3068"\w* \w rebuild|strong="H1129"\w* \w the|strong="H3588"\w* \w ruins|strong="H2723"\w*.”  
